PART 1Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî CREATE MODELS & MIGRATIONS

1Ô∏è‚É£ Create Category Model + Migration
üìå Command
php artisan make:model Category -m

app/Models/Category.php
database/migrations/xxxx_xx_xx_create_categories_table.php

Schema::create('categories', function (Blueprint $table) {
    $table->id();
    $table->string('name');
    $table->timestamps();
});

2Ô∏è‚É£ Create Product Model + Migration

php artisan make:model Product -m

app/Models/Product.php
database/migrations/xxxx_xx_xx_create_products_table.php

Schema::create('products', function (Blueprint $table) {
    $table->id();
    $table->string('name');
    $table->decimal('price', 8, 2);

    $table->foreignId('category_id')
          ->constrained()
          ->onDelete('cascade');

    $table->timestamps();
});

php artisan migrate

PART 2Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî DEFINE RELATIONSHIPS IN MODELS

3Ô∏è‚É£ Category Model (hasMany)

app/Models/Category.php

<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model;

class Category extends Model
{
    protected $fillable = ['name'];

    public function products()
    {
        return $this->hasMany(Product::class);
    }
}

4Ô∏è‚É£ Product Model (belongsTo)

app/Models/Product.php

<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model;

class Product extends Model
{
    protected $fillable = ['name', 'price', 'category_id'];

    public function category()
    {
        return $this->belongsTo(Category::class);
    }
}

PART 3Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî USING THE RELATIONSHIP

5Ô∏è‚É£ Create Product Under Category
$category = Category::find(1);

$category->products()->create([
    'name' => 'Laptop',
    'price' => 50000
]);

6Ô∏è‚É£ Get Products of a Category
$category = Category::find(1);

foreach ($category->products as $product) {
    echo $product->name;
}

7Ô∏è‚É£ Get Category from Product
$product = Product::find(1);
echo $product->category->name;

PART 4Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî CONTROLLER EXAMPLE

app/Http/Controllers/ProductController.php

use App\Models\Category;
use App\Models\Product;

class ProductController extends Controller
{
    public function index()
    {
        $categories = Category::with('products')->get();
        return view('products.index', compact('categories'));
    }
}

PART 5Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî BLADE VIEW EXAMPLE

resources/views/products/index.blade.php

@foreach($categories as $category)
    <h3>{{ $category->name }}</h3>

    @foreach($category->products as $product)
        <p>{{ $product->name }} - ‚Çπ{{ $product->price }}</p>
    @endforeach
@endforeach
